						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab built into Shamsuddin's well behind the Ashruf Khāna.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record, a broken piece, refers to the God Rāmanāthadēva, the city Poṭṭala cherla, and the two places Paṟagimaṭṭu and Naṟṟakallu.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
